'''Highway 40''' (also called '''Kananaskis Trail''' in [[Kananaskis, Alberta|Kananaskis Improvement District]], and '''Bighorn Highway''' in [[Bighorn No. 8, Alberta|M.D. of Bighorn]]) is a south-north highway located in western [[Alberta]]. It extends from the hamlet of [[Coleman, Alberta|Coleman]] in the [[Crowsnest Pass, Alberta|Municipality of Crowsnest Pass]] northward to the city of [[Grande Prairie, Alberta|Grande Prairie]], it currently has two gravel sections.

The first gravel section runs for approximately {{km to mi|102|abbr=yes}} from the Municipality of Crowsnest Pass to [[Alberta Highway 541|Highway 541]], and is currently marked as Highway 40. The second gravel section, which runs for approximately {{km to mi|293|abbr=yes}}, through the [[Rocky Mountains]] Forest is named [[Alberta Highway 734|Highway 734]], also called '''Forestry Trunk Road'''. The intention is that one day the entire road will be a continuous paved highway. In the past, other gravel sections were named Highway 940, the [[List of Alberta provincial highways#900 and X series|900 series]] in Alberta is used as temporary names.

